<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="SimpleMauiApp._7section">
    <ScrollView>
        <VerticalStackLayout>
            <!-- Chapter Title -->
            <Label 
                Text="The Evolution of Operating Systems"
                FontSize="24"
                FontAttributes="Bold"
                HorizontalOptions="Center"
                Margin="10" />

            <!-- Introduction -->
            <Label 
                Text="Operating Systems have undergone significant transformation since their inception. This chapter explores their journey, from early single-tasking systems to the sophisticated multi-user and distributed systems of today."
                FontSize="16"
                Margin="10"
                HorizontalTextAlignment="Center" />

            <!-- 1st Generation -->
            <Label 
                Text="1. First Generation (1940s-1950s): Manual Systems"
                FontSize="18"
                FontAttributes="Bold"
                Margin="10" />
            <Label 
                Text="Early computers lacked an OS. Programs were manually loaded using punch cards or paper tape. Each task required complete control of the hardware, making operation cumbersome."
                FontSize="16"
                Margin="10"
                HorizontalTextAlignment="Start" />
            <Label 
                Text="Example: ENIAC (Electronic Numerical Integrator and Computer)."
                FontSize="14"
                Margin="10"
                HorizontalTextAlignment="Start" />

            <!-- 2nd Generation -->
            <Label 
                Text="2. Second Generation (1950s-1960s): Batch Processing Systems"
                FontSize="18"
                FontAttributes="Bold"
                Margin="10" />
            <Label 
                Text="Batch processing introduced the concept of executing a series of jobs without user interaction. Programs were submitted as 'batches,' improving efficiency."
                FontSize="16"
                Margin="10"
                HorizontalTextAlignment="Start" />
            <Label 
                Text="Example: IBM 704, General Motors' GM-NAA I/O OS."
                FontSize="14"
                Margin="10"
                HorizontalTextAlignment="Start" />

            <!-- 3rd Generation -->
            <Label 
                Text="3. Third Generation (1960s-1970s): Multiprogramming and Time-Sharing"
                FontSize="18"
                FontAttributes="Bold"
                Margin="10" />
            <Label 
                Text="Multiprogramming allowed multiple programs to share the CPU, enhancing utilization. Time-sharing systems enabled interactive user sessions."
                FontSize="16"
                Margin="10"
                HorizontalTextAlignment="Start" />
            <Label 
                Text="Example: UNIX, IBM's OS/360."
                FontSize="14"
                Margin="10"
                HorizontalTextAlignment="Start" />

            <!-- 4th Generation -->
            <Label 
                Text="4. Fourth Generation (1980s-Present): Personal Computers"
                FontSize="18"
                FontAttributes="Bold"
                Margin="10" />
            <Label 
                Text="The advent of personal computers popularized OSs like MS-DOS, Windows, and macOS. Graphical User Interfaces (GUIs) became mainstream, making computers more accessible."
                FontSize="16"
                Margin="10"
                HorizontalTextAlignment="Start" />
            <Label 
                Text="Example: Windows 95, macOS."
                FontSize="14"
                Margin="10"
                HorizontalTextAlignment="Start" />

            <!-- 5th Generation -->
            <Label 
                Text="5. Fifth Generation (2000s-Present): Mobile and Cloud Systems"
                FontSize="18"
                FontAttributes="Bold"
                Margin="10" />
            <Label 
                Text="Modern OSs power mobile devices, cloud platforms, and IoT. These systems emphasize connectivity, real-time performance, and seamless user experiences."
                FontSize="16"
                Margin="10"
                HorizontalTextAlignment="Start" />
            <Label 
                Text="Example: Android, iOS, Linux-based cloud systems."
                FontSize="14"
                Margin="10"
                HorizontalTextAlignment="Start" />

            <!-- Summary -->
            <Label 
                Text="The evolution of Operating Systems showcases humanity's ingenuity in meeting the growing demands of technology. From manual systems to cloud-driven platforms, OSs continue to shape the digital world."
                FontSize="16"
                Margin="10"
                HorizontalTextAlignment="Center" />

            <!-- Next Button -->
            <Button
                Text="Continue"
                BackgroundColor="Blue"
                TextColor="White"
                FontAttributes="Bold"
                HorizontalOptions="Center"
                VerticalOptions="End"
                Margin="10"
                Clicked="NextClicked" />
        </VerticalStackLayout>
    </ScrollView>
</ContentPage>